Great professor!! Take his class!! Easy A if you put forth a little effort!!!

Great teacher, funny, gives real life examples. Uses power points in the class, they are helpful for open-book online tests.   Book is not mandatory, but helps on exams a lot. Great teacher who has a great sense of humor, and keeps class fun.The test are open book and online. There is one group project, and 3 case studies. All you have to do is try and you will get an A.

Take him if you need to take MGS 3400!

He's a great teacher and all of his exams are multiple choice.  If you take MGS 3400 take him, you will not go wrong.  You will have to read your book but that's because the final is departmental.  But other than that I enjoyed the class because he made it easy.
A great professor - who makes the class a fun one.

Dr. Yao is a great math professor, meticulous, delicate and devoted so much time to his teachings. Dr. Yao's lectures are long and drawn out but everything is digestible. 6 homeworks (25%), 2 tests(25% each), and a final(25%). He is very straight forward. Gives tons of homework which is really helpful. He answers all your questions and takes time to make sure you understand. Great Professor

comment: This professor does a real good job in teaching Modern Algebra.

GRADING: h/w 25%, two midterms 25% each, final 25%. H/w once a week, two midterms and the final exam. With enough effort everyone should get an A in the class.
Great lecturer. Really makes sure topics are clear and everyone understands.  Very kind man and really knowledgeable.  You're the best Professor!

Professor Yao is by far the best math professor I have ever had. He is  extremely clear and is a fair grader. He focuses on the important content of the subject. Tests are very similar to the homework. Go to class!

Professor Yao is eccentric and takes a little time to get used to. However, the man knows his stuff and explains it clearly. He may go off on a tangent sometimes by over explaining some topics but for the most part he's easy to follow.

Prof. Yao is the best. Modern algebra is a hard subject but Prof Yao makes it easier to digest the materials. HWs are mandatory in his class and tests are similar to his HWs.  Keep in mind that this is not an easy subject to get an A just like that. You'll be definitely awarded with the grade you deserve if you work hard.

I loved his class, all 3 i took with him. He teaches slowly, even too slowly alot of the time, but it's perfect because no one is left behind. He is very helpful and has lots of office hours. His tests are just like his HW.

This course was hard to do remote. We were graded on things we had to teach ourselves, like pronunciation. Lock down browser with camera was used for all exams. we completed 168 VHL assignments. Took many hours a week and a tutor I hired to get through it.

comment: Graybs is an interesting person with insightful anecdotes & personal experiences that emphasize his lessons. She is very nice and helpful. You should read the book and pay attention to her presentations. If you do that you will get an A
Professor is very helpful and nice.  She makes the class enjoyable.  She is a great professor.

comment: Good Professor. For a physics course, which is generally difficult, he mad it easier. Go to class, ask questions, utilize his office hours and do the labs. Lecture is confusing, homework is impossible, tests are as easy as 2+2. If you're not a physics major, TAKE DR. SARSOUR. He's funny, and is really inviting to students when they don't understand the homework. I can't say enough about how awesome he is.

I would recommend that you wait a semester or  take him only if you have to. He has a heavy accent and he is VERY intimidating for no reason. He is straight up mean. Smart man, but all he does in lecture is throw out formulas and showing how they are derived. After the first two weeks I was completely lost and extremely behind because of this.

I am so thankful to have had Dr. Sarsour as my first pre-med professor. He is very clear about what it takes to get an A in the class (read topics before class, do stop to think problems, understand concepts,etc.) He also gives students a lot of breaks  (drops lowest test grade, gives extra credit). I pray  the rest of my premed profs r lik hm.

He goes extremely quick, but he has to to cover all 16 chapters.  He's extremely helpful during his office hours, and has around 4-6 hours a week set aside to help students. Take advantage of this. Class is relatively easy if you have a strong math background. If not, study hard.
nice guy
He is good.
He is extremely Helpful. If We go to his office then he will help a lot. Classes are ok. He is also funny.

TAKE HIM! His lectures and notes are 100% from the book. Don't let his lectures intimidate you: GO TO OFFICE HOURS! He's always willing to help and won't stop until you get it. If you make an effort, you will do well in this class. I actually failed the 1st test, asked for his help, and I made an A in the class.

He's a really nice guy and extremely helpful. He wants all his students to do well and makes available over 6 hours a week outside of class to help students. Lack of effort would be the only reason anyone would fail this class.

He's really nice when he knows you want help. Phyics is generally hard if its not your world, but if your looking for "easy A" he's not the guy. Will not fail you if you ask for help and knows you are making an effort. And yes he has a really strong accent, but thats like 80 percent of science professors at state.

Physics is somewhat difficult regardless of who is teaching it. He is very, very helpful if you go to his office. Also, he takes into account your attendance and effort more than any of your grades. Best advice: Try hard, go to class (!!!) visit him a lot, and don't be rude!

This class is hard, you have to work, work, work. The homework is also hard, however if you come to his office hours he will help. Attendance isn't mandatory however it helps your grade at the end. Chapter quizzes, tests consist of 5 questions so study! The final was cumulative. He's not horribly bad, but not easy either--physics isn't easy period

ABSOLUTELY "THE" WORST TEACHER. He's so smart that it's hard for him to explain things in a simplified way. My whole class struggled, if not failed, in his class. His test are ridiculously hard, and he has like 18 quizzes. You MUST read the book and you will end up dedicating your life to Physics if you take this class. BEWARE if new to Physics!!!

not well understood, does not answer questions, doesn't try to make things easier for students. not accessible. doesn't like you to take notes, which is ridiculous. i would not take him or recommend him.

he's not easy to understand, and he goes really fast. doesn't explain very well. tests are super easy though, good with after-class help. just go over the notes, do problems in class & do homework and you'll be good for the tests! easy grader too!

A little difficult to understand due to accent. Brilliant man... somewhat difficult to keep up with - goes through the material during lectures extremely fast! Lectures are not mandatory but you must be there if you want any hope of understanding. happy to help you. encourages you to go to his office and i recommend it as well! show him your face!!

I am glad I passed the first time because I did not want to take research again. It's required for undergrad, but should really be an elective.

I was a student from one of the other classes that merged with her class. I just have to say that she is one of the rudest professors Ive ever met at GSU. She makes the class much harder than it needs to be as most of us are in the class (an elective) just so we can graduate. Not because we care about research. Class was unorganized too.

She literally is defensive about everything. She does not give clear rubrics for papers or in-class activities, yet she grades harshly. She will give you attitude in front of everyone in class if she feels attacked (EVEN IF IT'S JUST A QUESTION). She will constantly make you feel dumb if and provide the most meaningless feedback.

The tests are very hard. I wouldn't recommend this class to anyone. She is very sarcastic and she shows no concern for her student's grades. She grades harshly, her study guides are useless, and she uses the lockdown browser. This class is a lot harder than it should be. If you care about your grade you would choose a different professor.
homework is easy but the test are extremely hard . her study guide is crap and she make you use lockdown browser when taking your test

Donovan Ellis is my favorite professor I have ever had! He makes online class somehow SO interesting, and something that you are excited to attend unlike other classes/instructors. He truly cares about his students, and really makes a connection with each one in class. He makes each topic super easy to understand & is so passionate. TAKE HIM!!!!!

This class was super fun and Prof. Woods really shows how much she cares about her students. You always knew where you stood in the class because grades were given with super detailed feedback. I would definitely take Prof. Woods again!

Shes the best!! She wants her students to succeed in her class, so shes more than willing to help. You are graded by 4 hw assignments, 5 quizzes, the midterm & cumulative final. While her class is easy, it is not because of b.s. work. She is just an awesome prof. Her expectations are clear and she is more than willing to work with students to ensure that they understand. Her class reassured me I have chosen the right major!
Her teaching style isn't my favorite, but I think she's personable, and her classes aren't difficult. Her explanations and examples are very well done. I'm taking her again in the Spring!

comment: Very knowledgeable, very patient. She explains everything very thoroughly and uses easy to follow/study powerpoints. Her quizzes/tests are easy as long as you actually show up to class. I hope I get to take more classes with her in the future!

Awesome professor, the study guides he gives are the tests. So do them! :) Easy A.

GREAT TEACHER..... Great sense of humor he's really good

He has a thick accent, but as you stay in the class you are able to understand more clearly. He really does his best to make sure you understand the material. One of my classmates failed every test and still managed to make a B.... he's very understanding.
A great professor.

Nice man, THICK accent. He makes sure everyone understands the topic. Weekly homework and 4-5 tests. Very easy math but he makes sure every does understand. Its a boring class, but I got an A and thats all that really matters right
Great class for someone like me that is terrible at Math, I literally am so glas i read the reviews when picking teachers this semester.

Dr. Zhong is an amazing professor. If you're not a math major and aren't good at math then he's the professor for you. The study guides are literally the same as the test and the online textbook is very helpful because it gives step-by-step help on each problem. The online homework literally tells you exactly how to solve the problem and let's you re-try until you get it right. If you fail, it is 100% because you didn't try. Study guides pretty match tests & he gives partial credit. I am terrible at math & never though I'd get A's on tests! Highly recommend this professor.
Dr. Zhong is great. He is a professional in teaching analysis. He is able to break down the problem part by part so students are able to understand.
He is a very caring professor. He really cherish his students through his teachings. He is very detailed during help session. If you are willing to work hard for your grade, the result will be great.

2 MIDTERMS, and corrections for each (redo wrong parts to get 50% of the corrected missed points). TAKE-HOME TEST (few probs) towards the end of the semester. HW - given throughout the semester (it's in lecture notes... about 40 problems in all) - to submit at the FINAL EXAM day. > Grading: Midterm - 25% each, HW - 25%, Final - 25%.  TAKE HIM!

I wouldn't really ascribe any tags to this man. He isn't the best professor I had, but he is pretty good. His accent is funny at times, but you're definitely not going to be thinking to yourself "why am I sitting through this hell" or "this is the hardest thing I have ever done". Good class.

Solid professor , He gives a fair amount of partial credit , online homework and quizzes are easy, you really cant fail them unless you just don't do it . He gives extra credit if you do all the study guides , 1 random project to it was easy. Very hard to understand accent sometimes, but I really suck at math and still passed . So that says alot.
I loved this class. I have always had problems with math but I was finally able to get the hang of it. So easy!! I would take him again.

His accent is pretty thick; sit up close if you can. Stay on top of your HW; he collects it before exams. The exam questions are 5 problems similar to a few HW problems; focus on the more challenging HW problems. I've heard horror stories from Analysis, but this class wasn't too bad with Zhong. Definitely try to take analysis with him.
Dr. Zhong is a great professor to taka Analysis I. He is great at explaining material in an efficient way. Would take another proof course with him.

His English is not perfect, and his accent is rather strong. Fairly easy class, he is very helpful one-on-one, and he gives you credit for everything he can, even if the answers are wrong.

Dr. Zhong is an excellent professor. He explains the material so that you understand. He is patience, caring and wants you to get a good grade. He even provided help after class on material that I didn't understand. I had no problem understanding him at all.  I would recommend this professor.

Dr. Zhong is really nice and helpful to his students. His accent is STRONG, you won't really be able to understand what he's saying all the time in the beginning but you get used to it fast. He walks around the room to make sure each student gets the work. I would recommend him.

Dr. Zhong is an excellent professor. Not only does he give a thorough and clear explanation despite his accent, he also cares about his students. I can go as far to say that I actually enjoyed his class. I highly recommend him for Analysis I/II or any proof based course.

Performance in this class is a complete crapshoot. so easy if you do the homework. his tests are the same as the study guides he gives out but with different numbers and stuff.

He made a class that many people have trouble with accessible.  I would recommend him for analysis.

Dr. Zhong is boring. I couldn't understand a word he was saying. He never gave me a 100 on a test or project. He takes off points for things that are right. Don't buy the book. Awesome guy!!! If you are not a freshman, it can be a bit frustrating to sit in class with a bunch of kids (Math 1101 is a freshmen course) but Changyoung Professor was extremely helpful, and understanding of my math issues. I will take Math 1070 with him.

So I took this class online due to COVID. The course content was all in modules in icollege. Module organization is not clear - online readings and videos are located over multiple pages. All deadlines are on the syllabus but only half of them are located on iCollege calendar. There is a large group assignment that is the majority of your overall grade (better hope you get a good group). Tough grader but does provide detailed feedback.
He is a strict grader and assigns a lot of papers. His tests can be extremely hard and confusing. Overall, his class is bearable, but you will definitely have to put the work in.

Horrible !!!!! avoid this teacher you will have so much homework like PSYCH is your major heavy homework , heavy test that she doesn't give a lot of time to do heavy load of everything avoid this teacher she will fail you even if you do all the work and pass all of them she is a very tough grader it has to be a certain way if it isn't you will fail

I made an A and found it difficult because the material was difficult not him.  Also, you don't have to go to class his tests are straight from the book.

comment: This class requires a LOT of reading, 3 stories to write, 1 presentation, + 1 tough midterm. You will do a craft journal for everything you read and 1 homage per book. Im not here to diss him, hes actually a nice guy, but his course is demanding. So if this is an elective, do yourself a favor and keep looking. Also, theres a quiz every class.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES

comment: The hardest part about this class is having to read your stories aloud to receive feedback from peers, who can be more critical than Holman. He seems to care about each individual and gives good feedback. I feel better about my writing after taking his class and plan on taking his Senior Seminar.

Nice guy. Funny too. He makes the class fun. He is a somewhat harsh grader but let's you redo papers for better grade. Lots of papers. Book and attendance required. Forces you to participate in class. No tests. In class writing. Easy A.
Professor Holman is a great professor. He's very helpful, nice and easy to talk to about your writing. Good sense of humor too. Take him if you can!
Amazing professor. He's a really nice guy and makes you feel very comfortable discussing your writing with him and the rest of your peers. Very encouraging and helpful. I highly recommend him.
I enjoyed his teaching style. The class was comfortable, not to hard, not to easy. Holman is friendly and helpful.

Dr. Holman is extremely down-to-earth and prefers getting to know students over merely spoon-feeding  them information. The books he assigned were fantastic, especially if you're a fan of regional and'or postmodernist fiction. Fun class.

This is a great class. He's funny, knowledgable, and the assignments really make you think about how you write. The workload is not too heavy, but it's enough to get you even more interested in writing, especially different ways of writing. Highly highly recommended.

He's very nice, accessible, loves his subject, and is very understanding. Definitely one of the better teachers to have for online learning. You only really need to take notes on what is in the powerpoint, but always listen to the lectures. As long as you can pass the chapter quizzes you should be okay.
ratingTags: Accessible outside class--Get ready to read--Caring

comment: Dr. White is awesome because he makes astronomy fascinating. You can see how he lights up when he talks about this stuff, and that passion translates into great, engaging lectures that explain everything really clearly. You dont have to attend them to get an A, either, because his powerpoints are just as clear and detailed.

I didn't go to class after the first test (on which I got a 100) and also didn't do any of the reading/all of the homeworks and still managed to finish with a B+. His lectures (those I went to) were good. Two expensive books needed for the class. A lot of boring basic physics material. Takes a while to get grades back. One dropped test.

He believes that everyone in that class is as passionate about astronomy as he is. trust me, theyre not. The test are ridiculous, and he is the only professor i know that makes his final cumulative. He gives study guides that are like 60 questions long and every question has like 3-5 questions in it, so if you think about it, it isnt of much help.

Really passionate and knowledgable about the material! He teaches using PowerPoints which he uploads online. Attendance wasn't mandatory but is helpful because he will explain concepts in detail. Tests are multiple choice and you will get an A if you review using his study guides.
ratingTags: ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Clear grading criteria--Amazing lectures

comment: He gives study guides on what is NOT on the test. I blew off the first test but the next two i tried and i studied the practice quiz and i still failed there was one question i knew He rewords it to complicated. The class is all him talking and rambling on and on about one topic then to the next slide and repeat. I attended every class got a C.

I took a couple of his classes when he taught at UAH.  He is amazing!  I had a huge crush on him and seriously reconsidered my major because of him.  BUT he moved to GSU!  Bummer!  I would totally recommend him though.  He used a lot of pictures to explain topics, which helped a lot.  I love his passion for astronomy, and it shows during lectures.

He's really excited about the material, but he gets too frantic and it's hard to understand him or he flips to through the power point too quickly. He'll help you a whole lot if you ask for it, whatever the case may be. ATTENDANCE IS MANDATORY FOR AN A. He'll clearly express whats on the test and homework in class. If you don't go, you'll suffer.

One of my favorite professors so far. Taught the subject well and gave extra credit on each test. Do the study guides and you'll do well on the tests. Online homework once a week but it's easy - all of the answers are online. Would definitely recommend taking his class.

Failed all the test(62,62,66) got a 120 on the all the homework(answers online),did well on Labs(buy used from bookstore,or if you can,share the book w/ someone and make copies).book comes with mandatory access code,Got a B+.hated the subject and still do, but if i can do this horrible and get a B+ you can do a lil better for an A/A+

My favorite professor to date at GSU! Made astronomy interesting and meaningful. Clear in explaining concepts and helpful with questions. Weekly online homework helped with understanding new material. PowerPoints during his lectures, but they're not boring! Gives study guide for all tests that can be solved by reviewing posted PPTs.

Hands down the most awesome professor at GSU! Taught the subject well. Didn't need the book as all the info is provided on the power points. Labs can be boring and depending on your TA they may grade harshly, but just do the HW and well on the tests and you'll get an easy A.
Easy A! Did not use the book at all. Study the power points for the test and you'll do well!
Most amazing teacher ever. he makes it so easy and interesting.

Pretty easy and straight forward class. I bought the book but ended up not needing it at all. You do have homework that you have to do once a week online, and there are only like 3 tests. Read the book, and pay attention every so often in class and you'll do fine. The lab is "eh". You have to go to an observatory away from school which is a pain.

Russell is an amazing teacher. I had little interest in ASTR before this class, but he actually made me consider changing my major to learn more. His lectures are entertaining and really clarify some of the more burdensome topics of the book. He gives reviews and old tests to help you prepare for each test; each test will take less than 20 minutes.

I really enjoyed this class. Although attendance is not mandatory, the reading material may be a bit unclear without his power-points an explanations. He tends to ramble and say "Um" a lot, but as long as you copy the power-points (they are not online) and use the study guide prior to the test, you will be fine. Don't forget the online homework!
He's very jumpy and tends to not finish his sentences, but as long as you get the notes from the powerpoint you'll be fine.

GREAT PROFESSOR!!!! he is extremely clear on assignments and notes so when the test comes around u know exactly what u need to know to do well. Very available and knows alot about the subject!!! you will do well if u try!!!! :) cant recommend him enough!!!!!!!

Prof. White is very helpful. The lecture notes are clear and he has a very pleasant demeanor. His tests are multiple choice and straitforward. Overall he is a good professor. The labs are tedious and mandatory.(Bummer)

He's a nice guy but he puts so much information on the study guides it's nearly impossible to figure out what you really need to study. Don't take him in the morning because you'll fall asleep. He drops one test grade which is nice but, I got mainly C's even though I studied really hard which was annoying. Overall, he was okay.
I actually missed more days than I came to class and got a B. He gives good study guides for test and the only other grade is lab and easy web assignments.

his powerpoints explained things clearly and i can tell he has a lot of enthusiasm and knowledge behind what he teaches.  i found it difficult to understand him sometimes because he does get a little rambly. but he follows the book exactly.

he uses power points to teach and they are the only thing you really need for the tests.  there are online homeworks everyweek that the book answers without having to read it easy skim to find answers. answers all questions, great teacher, i signed up for him for astronomy 1020 because i enjoyed the class so much!!

He's a funny guy and is obviously very intelligent. His cold calls are a bit scary since he dwells on one person per case, so you need to be prepared. Readings aren't bad and he wraps up concepts nicely to ensure everyone understands what the point of the case was.

If you read the only the cases he assigns he will make you think that the U.S. Constitution is actually the Communist Manifesto. He will try to indoctrinate you into being a liberal democrat. Don't fall for it, read the actual Constitution and the cases he does not assign. It is easy to get a good grade without reading if you agree with him.

Kinkopf is not someone I will recommend. He is arrogant, and he wants to show you that you are not up to his level. His exam is completely different from his lectures. In addition, he is least generous with his grading.
Kinkopf is awesome. I was not looking forward to the class beforehand, and ended up loving it.

Greatest professor I've ever had. The man is simply brilliant. He doesn't let you get away with semi-right answers like most professors. He forces you to think not only about why the right answer is right, but also why the wrong answer is wrong. You might get slightly embarrassed in class, but that's clearly not his intention. Take Kinkopf.

Face it, he will be too smart for you. He will ask probing questions in such an innocuous way that you feel as if the answer shoudl be obvious. He's a great professor though, and he really gets into the heart of issues like no other professor I took. Tough semester but I was rewarded for hard work. I will be taking him in the fall for Con Law.
Very smart and interesting.  Does go beyond most people's comprehension but worth taking.
I've had him for a number of classes.  He is really incredibly smart.

Great professor.  What the other rater calls "going off the deep end" I call "discussing nuances of the material."  If you want a comprehensive and fascinating examination of constitutional law, this is the guy.

Due to his complete mastery of the material, he frequently goes so far off the deep end in his discussions that it is practically impossible to understand what you just talked about in class. His exams are mind numbingly hard and leave you wondering, "What the hell just happened?" However, Ivory Tower as he may be, he has a decent sense of humor.

First I would recommend taking Snape if you are interested in applying to the BFA program but he is really picky. He critiques a lot and expects you to have a lot of sketches. He also does give a lot of work but its something to prepare you in the future I guess. He always checks up on everyone on their progress which is good.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Accessible outside class--Lecture heavy

comment: During COVID-19 and online classes, he's become lenient towards the amount of process work we submit for every project and mainly grades on craftsmanship and whether or not our design is efficient/creative. He's only helpful if you give him a lot of sketches/ideas to work with, otherwise, he doesn't know what you're thinking. Easy yet stressful.

Snape pushes you to think beyond your first idea. Ive learned a lot from him in the way that I approach process, critical thinking and analysis. Many students tend to first come into to the class thinking they need to create something beautiful/Behance-worthy, but he really emphasizes finding, exploring and loving the process.

Brilliant graphic design instructor at Georgia State. He is thorough, inspirational and hard working. He challenges the general standards of art and design and pushes you to create the most strong and compelling designs. His feedback is always great and he is truly one of the best professors I've had in my college career.

I took his class before and I am taking his class again. I think he is an amazing professor. It's hard to make him satisfy because he always wants more idea for your design. comment: A great professor who knows how to teach. Classes are based around few assignments, but you get a lot of time to work on it in-class and out. Snape gives good feedback and individually works with you to help you succeed.

Snape's class is enjoyable and he brings a good attitude to class everyday but I do have to agree with the last post. A lot of the work he assigns is unnecessary. He can be helpful if you're a beginner, wouldn't recommend it for anyone at an intermediate level or above.

to the last post: most students in his class are GRD majors so it IS very important. Snape is an extremely tough grader, but hasn't been involved in portfolio review process yet, so there's that. comment: DO NOT TAKE THIS PROFESSOR! DOESNT KNOW HOW TO TEACH COLLEGE. NOT CLEAR AND NOT CARING. SHES MEAN AND DOESNT FOLLOW HER OWN GRADING SYSTEM. SHE DOESNT USE THE SYLLABUS LIKE EVERY OTHER PROFESSOR. NO SET SCHEDULE SHE DOES IT ALL LAST MINUTE!

FUN

His test are ridiculously difficult for an elective class that doesn't even matter too much. He was very sarcastic and told corny jokes. He was very annoying because I tried so hard and still didnt do well on his test. FIND ANOTHER PROFESSOR!!!!!

Good professor overall, funny and makes the class interesting at the beginning. It starts to get boring, he curves tests but they're a bit hard. The speech helps your grade

he is a good teacher. knows what he is talking about. his test are way harder than they need to be and studying doesn't always help but he curves like 15-20 pts.

he's a figure skater!

Hilarious, friendly, and relatable. Gives curves and extra credit. Make sure you go to class and read the book, though. I would definitely take him again!

Great professor who teaches the class very well. He's really easy and gives lots of opportunities for students to do well in his class. Take him!

Great Teacher. If you are going to take speech 1000 take him. Please do. test are easy. only 3 test, but he gave us 20 point curve on 2 of them. especially take him if you have hard classes and need a laid back class.

nice guy, easy to understand, great lecturer, three speeches and one final exam... he was a little bit of a pushover when it came to keeping dates on certian assignments to avoid confusion but other than that hes awesome.

great teacher! 3 tests a speech and some online quizzes (very very easy). he curves tests and everything is from the powerpoints from lectures. TAKE HIM!!!

Pretty boring class at the end.

great

EASY EASY!! Didnt read a page in the book. take really DETAILED notes and you'll get an A. She doesn't make you do dates, and the only assignment other that film Q&A and the 3 tests the whole semester is one essay on a history subject of your choice. Take her shes funny.

Prof. Patterson is great! She knows a lot about history and doesnt make you memorize dates. She has a lot of quizzes over films to help your grade, three tests, and one film analysis which is easy and fun. She is a really good lecturer and made me actually enjoy history!

Professor Patterson is a great teacher. Attendance is mandatory. I don't like taking history classes but she makes you want to come to class. Prof. Patterson knows her stuff. A very nice lady! Read in advance for pop quizzes, take thorough notes, come to class and you'll have no problem making an A. There was one 5 page paper, but it is a no brainer and she grades leniently.
Very easy going.  Listen and take good notes. There will be plenty of notes to take.  Easy course if you listen.

Great professor. Very knowledgeable and helpful. Teaches from social and cultural perspective- no dates to memorize. Lots of videos and small quizzes to help out grade. One paper- film analysis that was actually pretty cool. Easy tests. Good study guides. Highly recommended.
very sweet lady. EASY tests! teaches from a cultural and social aspect. no date memorization!

She taught really well online during the COVID-19 pandemic. She's super nice and her lectures were clear and easy to understand. There are two oral exams for 1002, which made me nervous, but she is very lenient and patient when it comes to these.

comment: Professor Lin was very helpful with the material by making sure to practice with us because she wants us to succeed in this class.

Dr. Lin was always willing to provide help and feedback. I felt her genuine desire to help me advance and improve my Chinese. Based on our interactions I felt I had the support I needed to continue my Chinese learning above and beyond. She's AMAZING!

After this class I wish I could take all of my Chinese classes with Dr. Lin. Dr. Lin was considerate of her students needs and wanted to see us really learn. Lin Laoshi is very knowledgable. She understood that this was a beginner's Chinese course, so she provided ample accommodation. She was always well prepared and fair. Dr. Lin is a sweet lady. Class wasn't too hard as long as you did the readings and kept up with the work. The readings were really interesting!
Dr. Lin is so kind, thorough, and organized. It is so easy to be high-achieving when our instructor sets us up for success.

comment: This was by far my favorite class of this year, my favorite teacher, and probably my favorite for both of those categories of all of my years in college (three years now, plus two years of dual enrollment). comment: The class is boring, but discrete math isn't that much of an interesting subject. He has a sense of humor and  grades very leniently. The overall grade consists of 5 tests. Dr Hall is extremely willing to help and a very lenient grader. I had two classes with him, and he is ridiculously difficult. In Linear Algebra, he failed half the class, including several with D+. I took Discrete Mathematics with him, and it was harder than Bridge with another professor. He instructs well, but his grading is brutal!!!

Good professor, makes discrete mathematics doable. Take notes and do homework, and tests will be fairly easy. The problems come straight from the homework and notes. TAKE NOTES! READ THE BOOK! If you do those and review them well, the tests will be relatively easy. It's a hard class, but doing the homework and taking notes (cliche, I know) will take you very far. His teaching is extremely boring, but staying conscious will pay off in the end.

Hall lectures really really reaaaally slow. I had to teach myself a bunch of the sections, but his tests are reasonable. In Calc you HAVE to do your homework, which he's good about going over, but it will take most of the class.

comment: Dr. Rizzo is by far one of the best professors that you'll come across at GSU. I just finished calc II with an A+ and its all thanks to her preparing me for it.  Definitely take her!

Professor Rizzo is AMAZING. I haven't had a math professor who was this enthused and loved what they do in a while. Rizzo is great! She really wants you to learn and she will do all she can to help you. She wants you to learn and understand the material rather than just memorize it. I would most definitely take her class again if I could. She's one of the best teachers I've ever had.
good

Dr. Rizzo is an awesome teacher! You can tell she wants you to succeed and she has a natural desire for not only teaching, but constantly learning as well. Go to class. Do the homework. Take advantage of extra credit. She's really passionate and entertaining in the way she teaches the material.
